metadata.name: TWO WORLDS APART
metadata.description:
“Two Worlds Apart”  
Can anybody find me?  
I’m still where I used to be  
It seems like no one’s looking  
But I feel that I’ll be free

I know that I’m not like them  
And they know they’re not like me 
But I’d like to keep it that way  
And I feel no jealousy

Those that used to be our shields  
Have now picked up their swords  
And when we used to walk away  
There is no way but towards

Poem by Luca Ponsato
